== Festivities ==
[[File:4 de 7 de germanor a Colles de l'Eix.jpg|thumb|Fraternity [[4 in 7]] in Salt]]
The calendar Marrecs follow each year has five special highlights: two annual ones in Salt (''Festa Major'' and ''Colles de l'Eix''), two annual ones in Girona ([[Diada de Sant Narcís|Sant Narcís]] and the walking walking pillar of the Cathedral) and the [[Tarragona Human Tower Competition|Human Tower Competition]], held in Tarragona biannually every even year and to which they have attended seven times until 2014.<ref name="editionsCompetition" /> The ''Festa Major'' performance in Salt falls at the end of July and it marks the end of the first stretch of the season. It is the most important performance held in Salt.<ref name="twoCities" />

''Colles de l'Eix'' is a brotherhood performance taking place each September and it always involves Marrecs with [[Tirallongues de Manresa]], [[Castellers de Lleida]] and [[Sagals d'Osona]] performaing alternatively in Salt, [[Manresa]], [[Lleida]] and [[Vic]], the respective home towns, which are united by the ''[[Eix transversal]]'' (Catalan for "cross axis") since this road was built in 1997. Starting on its very first edition back in 1999 in Manresa, it is a tradition to end the performance with a brotherhood [[4 in 7]], a tower build with a quarter of the base and one row of each of the participating groups, making with the different colors of the shirts (blue, stripped blue, burgundy and orange), a colourful and unusual tower.<ref>{{cite news|title=Castells de germanor: més que una imatge|publisher=Revista Castells|url=http://revistacastells.cat/2013/09/castells-de-germanor-mes-que-una-imatge/|date=12 September 2013|language=catalan}}</ref>

''Diada de Sant Narcís'' is starred by Marrecs and [[Minyons de Terrassa]] since 1996, and since 2007 also by [[Capgrossos de Mataró]]. Apart from the fact that Marrecs have reached some of their best performances in this festivity, it is specially remarkable some of the milestones by Minyons de Terrassa, which in 1998 comp`leted the first [[4 in 9 with single base]] of the 20th century and their first [[pillar of 7 with double base]]<ref name="1r 2d7 99 i 4d9sf minyons 98">{{cite news|title=Els castells de nou protagonitzen la diada castellera de les Fires de Girona.|publisher=[[Vilaweb]]|url=http://www.vilaweb.cat/noticia/1116650/19991024/castells-protagonitzen-diada-castellera-fires-girona.html|date=24 October 1999|language=catalan}}</ref> and in 2008 their first [[pillar of 8 with triple base]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Els Minyons regalen un històric pilar de vuit amb folre i manilles a la plaça del Vi|publisher=[[Diari de Girona]]|url=http://www.diaridegirona.cat/elementosWeb/gestionCajas/DGI/File/fires(1).pdf|date=27 October 2008|language=catalan}}</ref>

''The walking pillar of the cathedral'', usually takes place on 1 November, and it is celebrated since 1997 in the [[cathedral of Girona]] and it is different to any other performance because Marrecs build a tower in the base of the stairway, then they walk a [[pillar of 4]] along the 90 steps and a last tower is built in front of the facade of the cathedral .<ref name="pillarofthecatedral" /><ref name=ddgsteps1997>{{cite news|last1=A. A.|title=Els Marrecs assoleixen l'objectiu després de 90 graons d'emoció|publisher=Diari de Girona|url=http://streaming.ajgirona.org/pandora/cgi-bin/Pandora.exe?xslt=show_pdf;publication=Diari%20de%20Girona;sort_publication=diari.de.girona;day=02;month=11;year=1997;page=014;id=0000189199;filename=19971102;collection=pages;url_high=pages/Diari%20de%20Girona/1997/199711/19971102/19971102014.pdf;lang=ca;pdf_parameters=search=%2290%20graons%20d%27emocio%22&view=FitH;encoding=utf-8|date=2 November 1997|language=catalan}}</ref> In 2010, being the last performance of a bad season,<ref name=important2012>{{cite news|last1=Comas|first1=Ure|title=L'important, quan un cau, és tornar-se a aixecar|publisher=El Punt Avui|url=http://streaming.ajgirona.org/pandora/cgi-bin/Pandora.exe?xslt=show_pdf;publication=Punt%20Avui,%20El;sort_publication=punt.avui.el;day=17;month=07;year=2012;page=048;id=0003020591;filename=20120717;collection=pages;url_high=pages/Punt%20Avui,%20El/2012/201207/20120717/20120717048.pdf;lang=ca;pdf_parameters=search=%22ho%20portem%20dins%22&view=FitH;encoding=utf-8|date=17 July 2012|language=catalan}}</ref> the pllar collapsed and it had to be rebuilt just to walk a few steps left, surrounded by the applauses of the audience.<ref>{{cite news|last1=T.C.C.|title=Els Marrecs pugen el pilar de 4 a la Catedral|publisher=Diari de Girona|url=http://streaming.ajgirona.org/pandora/cgi-bin/Pandora.exe?xslt=show_pdf;publication=Diari%20de%20Girona;sort_publication=diari.de.girona;day=01;month=11;year=2011;page=006;id=0002685374;filename=20111101;collection=pages;url_high=pages/Diari%20de%20Girona/2011/201111/20111101/20111101006.pdf;lang=ca;pdf_parameters=search=%22els%20marrecs%20van%20aconseguir%20pujar%20amb%20pilar%20quatre%20escales%20catedral%22&view=FitH;encoding=utf-8|date=1 November 2011|language=catalan}}</ref> The journalist, and member of the group, Ester Bertran<ref>{{cite web|title=Get up again once and again|publisher=Forum impulsa|url=http://en.forumimpulsa.org/2012/impulsa-forum-2012/articles/get-up-again-once-and-again/}}</ref> released the video ''Ho portem dins'' (''It is inside us'' in English), that soon became viral.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Redacció|title=Esclata a la xarxa el vídeo 'Ho portem dins' com a metàfora del moment que viu el país|publisher=Vilaweb|url=http://www.vilaweb.cat/noticia/4058338/20121124/esclata-xarxa-video-ho-portem-dins-metafora-moment-viu-pais.html|date=24 November 2012|language=catalan}}</ref>

Marrecs have participated in seven editions of the biannual [[Tarragona Human Tower Competition]]. They became #18 in the 17th edition (1998), #7 in the 19th (2002), #13 in the 20th (2004), #11 in the 21st (2006), #12 in the 22nd (2008), #21 in the 24th (2012) and #16 in the 25th (2014).<ref name="editionsCompetition">{{cite web|url=http://www.concursdecastells.cat/edicions-anteriors-cdc|title=Edicions Anteriors|editor=[[Tarragona Human Tower Competition]]|language=catalan}}</ref> Their best performance was in 2014, but their best position happened in 2002, with a 7th position thanks to a [[4 in 8]], a [[2 in 7]] and an undone attempt of a [[3 in 8]] and an unprecedented [[pillar of 6]] crowned.<ref>{{cite news|title=Els Marrecs, setens a Tarragona|publisher=[[El Punt]]|date=14 October 2002|language=catalan}}</ref>

