== Awards ==
[[File:Placa dedicada als Marrecs a l'Ajuntament de Salt 2013.jpg|thumb|Commemorative plate in [[Salt]]]]
In 1998 the city council of Salt awarded them with the ''3 de març'' award for being a remarkable institution working for the village.<ref>{{cite news|title=Els premis de la independència|publisher=[[El Punt]]|url=http://www.elpuntavui.cat/noticia/article/-/5-societat/623852-els-premis-de-la-independencia.html|date=3 March 1998|language=catalan}}</ref> In 2003, ''Ateneu d'Acció Cultural'' awarded them with the ''normalització lingüística'' award.<ref>{{cite news|title=L'ADAC lliura el premi a la normalització lingüística|publisher=[[Vilaweb]]|url=http://www.vilaweb.cat/noticia/703398/20030605/noticia.html|date=5 June 2003|language=catalan}}</ref> In 2009 they were awarded as ''Gironí de l'any''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nit de premis |url=http://www.elpuntavui.cat/noticia/article/13-comunicacio/20-comunicacio/35499-nit-de-premis.html|publisher=[[El Punt]]|date=9 May 2009}}</ref> In 2010 [[Federació d'Ateneus de Catalunya]] gave them the ''Ateneus'' award for their social and cultural activities, thanks to the project of integration of the [[Senegal]] immigrants in Salt, mixing traditional activities of the Catalan people with music form the Senegalese association of musicians Oudiodial.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toc de castells als Premis Ateneus 2010|url=http://www.laxarxa.com/noticia/173701|publisher=[[La Xarxa]]|date=24 December 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140312213705/http://www.laxarxa.com/noticia/173701|archivedate=12 March 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

In 2002, the city council of Girona placed a plate in ''Plaça del Vi'' to commemorate the [[4 in 8]] and the crowned [[3 in 8]] of the performance of Sant Narcís  the previous.<ref name="4d8 3d8c 29 oct 2001">{{cite web |first1=Imma|last1=Bosch |url=http://www.vilaweb.cat/www/elpunt/noticia?p_idcmp=-64115 |title=Els Marrecs fan el seu primer castell de vuit |publisher=[[VilaWeb]] |date=29 October 2001 |language=catalan}}</ref> In 2002, the city council of Salt placed a plate in Lluís Companys square to commemorate the first tower of eight level ever completed in the village.<ref name="18yo" /> On 27 April 2014, matching the performance of the 18 years of the group, the city council of Salt, added another plate to commemorate the first performance of Marrecs with three completed towers of eight levelsa,which happened 28 July 2013.<ref name="18yo">{{cite news|title=Homenatge als Marrecs de Salt, que fan 18 anys|publisher=[[El Punt Avui]]|url=http://www.elpuntavui.cat/noticia/article/2-societat/5-societat/736422-els-tres-castells-de-8-del-28-de-juliol.html?cca=1|date=28 April 2014|language=catalan}}</ref>

In 2016 the [[Girona]] council chooses the Marrecs de Salt as the toastmasters of the local fest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.diaridegirona.cat/girona/2016/10/29/marrecs-salt-prego-dalcada-defensen/811810.html|title=Els Marrecs de Salt fan un pregó d'alçada i defensen la cultura popular|last=|first=|date=Diari the Girona - newspaper|website=|publisher=Diari the Girona - newspaper|access-date=2016-11-15}}</ref> Marrecs were also responsible for commemorating the 600th anniversary of the [[Gothic architecture|Gothic]] nave of the [[Girona Cathedral|Cathedral of Girona]]; on 1 November, after the traditional climbing of the stairs with a pillar of 4, the ''colla castellera'' raised a 3 in 8 and a pillar of 6 in the Gothic nave of the cathedral.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.diaridegirona.cat/girona/2016/11/02/marrecs-alcen-3d8-pilar-6/812432.html|title=Els Marrecs alcen un 3d8 i un pilar de 6 a dins la Catedral|last=|first=|date=Diari de Girona - newspaper|website=|publisher=Diari de Girona - newspaper|access-date=2016-11-15}}</ref>

